1. Install nvm


shortcut:

nvm use 16.19.1

nvm alias default 16.19.1

2. Install PostgresSQL

https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-and-use-postgresql-on-centos-7

After Instalation
    1.  [Change Password]
        sudo -i -u postgres
        psql
        \password
        sudo systemctl restart postgresql-11

    2.  [Open Port]
        firewall-cmd --add-service=postgresql --permanent
        firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=5432/tcp
        firewall-cmd --reload

    3.  [MODIFY FILE] :: vi /var/lib/pgsql/11/data/postgresql.conf
        listen_addresses = '*' => Uncomment this
            
    4.  (Optional) [ADD ACCESS / Whitelist] :: vi /var/lib/pgsql/11/data/pg_hba.conf
        example :
        #host    all             all             [IP]/32                md5 => Format
        host    all             all             118.136.198.241/32     md5
        host    all             all             0.0.0.0/0              md5             #For All IP

    5.  sudo systemctl restart postgresql-11

3. TODO: Install lsyncd [Server Directory Synchronization]

4. Install NodeJS and NPM
    1.  curl -sL https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_16.x | sudo -E bash -

    2.  sudo yum install nodejs

    3.  node -v

    4.  npm -v

    5. yum install gcc-c++ make -y

5.  Install pm2
    1.  npm install pm2@^3 -g

    2. pm2 startup systemd

6.  Install Git
    1.  sudo yum install git

    2.  git --version

    3.  git config --global user.name "Polly Markurin"

    4.  git config --global user.email "markurin.polly@gmail.com"

7. Install NGINX
    1.  yum install epel-release -y 

    2.  yum install nginx

    3.  systemctl start nginx

    4.  systemctl status nginx

    5. systemctl enable nginx

    6.  firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=http

    7.  firewall-cmd --reload

    8.  sudo setsebool -P httpd_can_network_relay on

    9.  sudo setsebool -P httpd_can_network_connect on

    NOTE:
        1. [Configuration] vi /etc/nginx/nginx.conf

        Revese Proxy for NodeJS Configuration example

        server {
            listen       80;
            listen       [::]:80;
            server_name  http://58.65.241.123;
            root         /usr/share/nginx/html;

            # Load configuration files for the default server block.
            include /etc/nginx/default.d/*.conf;

            location / {

                proxy_pass http://58.65.241.123:8281;

                proxy_http_version 1.1;

                proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;

                proxy_set_header Connection 'upgrade';

                proxy_set_header Host $host;

                proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;

            }

        error_page 404 /404.html;
        location = /404.html {
        }

        error_page 500 502 503 504 /50x.html;
        location = /50x.html {
        }
    }

8.  Open and Close firewall port

    firewall-cmd --zone=public --permanent --add-port=8281/tcp
    firewall-cmd --reload

    firewall-cmd --zone=public --permanent --remove-port=8281/tcp
    firewall-cmd --reload
